"&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from the Department for Transport (HRS 038)\n&#xa0;\nDuring \nthe\n recent\n Transport Select Committee hearing on High Speed Rail which took place on Tuesday 26 November, I promised to provide written evidence to the Committee detailing the basis of our revised estimates of business travellers. \nAnnex A fulfils this promise and co\nntains a detailed description of the approach taken and how it differs from the previous methodology.\n&#xa0;\nAnnex A&#xa0;The Approach to Forecasting HS2 Demand by Journey Purpose&#xa0;Why journey purpose matters\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nEstimation of journey purpose splits pri\nor to October 13\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe new \napproach to estimating journey purpose splits\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFigure 1: Change in proportion of 2010 weekday business rail travel by flow\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nComparison with Other Data Sources\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nProportion of weekday rail journeys in 2010 undertaken for business purposes August 12 ModelNational Travel SurveyPDFHv5October 13ModelLondon to East Midlands, Yorkshire and Humberside\n22%\n41%\n50%\n40%\nLondon to West Midlands and \nNorth West\n24%\n42%\n50%\n50%\nTable 1: Proportion of 2010 weekday business rail travel by flow (excluding weekend travel)\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0; \nhttp://www.dft.gov.uk/webtag/documents/expert/pdf/U3-5-6D-values-of-time-and-vehicle-operating-costs-Oct%202013.pdf\n Ticket\n sales data is taken from a rail industry ticket sales database known as LENNON\n.\n National Rail Travel Survey was undertaken by the SRA and \nDfT\n, and comprises the London Area Travel Surveys conducted in 2001 with additional surveys outside London conducte\nd in 2004 and 2005. \nhttp://assets.dft.gov.uk/statistics/series/rail/nrtsupdate.pdf\n \nDfT\n \nWebTAG\n Unit 3.154, Section 4.2. \nhttp://www.dft.gov.uk/webtag/documents/expert/pdf/u3_15_4-rail-passenge-demand-forecasting-120723.pdf\n \n \n The National Passenger Survey is\n undertaken by Passenger Focus and comprises periodic surveys designed to collect information on satisfaction with rail services but also includes details such as journey purpose. \nhttp://www.passengerfocus.org.uk/research/national-passenger-survey-introduction\n Note that the proportions in the graph are generally higher than those actually used in the appraisal due to the use of \nannualisation\n factors to multip\nly different journey purposes to annual totals and take account of weekend and bank holiday travel.\n The National Travel Survey is undertaken annually by the Department for Transport and is the primary source of data on personal travel patterns in Great B\nritain\nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-travel-survey-statistics\n Model used to generate the August 2012 HS2 economic case was known as PFMv3 \nhttp://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/120921_modelling%20development%20report%20v3%20final.pdf\n Model used to gene\nrate the October 2013 HS2 economic case was known as PFMv4.3\n \nhttp://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inse\nrts/S%26A%204_PLANET%20framework%20model%20%28PFM%20v4.3%29_model%20description.pdf\n"